text: October unemployment rates ranged from 1.9% in NE to 7.3% in CA and NV.
In Q3 2021, 24 states saw their greatest annual house price growth in three decades.
Retail employment in October 2021 was above prepandemic levels in 23 states.
GDP growth between Q2 2020 and Q2 2021 ranged from 6.6% in Alaska to 18.1% in Tennessee.
Among states, average private weekly earnings in October ranged from $802 in MS to $1,268 in MA.
Michigan and 35 other states saw manufacturing GDP exceed prepandemic levels in Q2 2021.
From Q3 2020 to Q3 2021, house price increases ranged from 8.0% in DC to 35.8% in ID.
NE, OK, and UT saw their lowest unemployment rates in 45 years in October 2021.
State and local public jobs in October 2021 were above prepandemic levels only in Idaho.
In Q2 2021, Washington State saw the highest growth in total GDP from prepandemic levels.
